{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Public inquiry into the selling of Family Asset Protection Trusts.",
        "additional_details": "We think the Government is not doing enough at the moment, and that this could be the Next Big Miss-Selling Scandal.\r\n \r\nWe think vulnerable people - such as the elderly and the sick - may be being sold these without their effects being properly explained, and that they can leave people worse off.  We believe they are being promised protection from costs - such as care fees - but that what they are being sold may not actually protect them from these costs. We want to see the government hold a public inquiry on this.",
        "background": "We think some people are being mis-sold \"Family Asset Protection Trusts\". We think the Government needs to protect citizens, introduce harsher punishments for miss-selling, and support victims. ",
